      "title": "Market Prices",
      "text": "Market Prices\n\n- Home\n- Market Information\n- Market Prices\n\n# Market Prices\n\nERCOT provides both Day-Ahead Market (DAM) prices on a daily basis and Real-Time Market (RTM) prices on an interval basis. Additionally, ERCOT has compiled DAM and RTM Settlement Point Prices (SPPs) for each of the Hubs and Load Zones by calendar year.\n\nERCOT monitors DAM, SCED, and SASM prices for errors. Price corrections are performed by ERCOT without the ERCOT Board's approval if done before the market prices are final. After the market prices are final, if ERCOT determines that prices are in need of correction, it shall notify Market Participants and describe the need for such correction. Market prices cannot be changed unless the ERCOT Board finds that the prices are significantly affected by a software or data error.\n\n## Day-Ahead and Real-Time Displays\n\nThe Locational Marginal Pricing (LMP) Contour Map offers a dynamic view of Real-Time resource node LMPs and both Day-Ahead Market and Real-Time Settlement Point Prices throughout the ERCOT region.\n\nReal-Time Market Clearing Prices for Capacity\n\nView the Market Clearing Price for Capacity (MCPC) for each ancillary service including Regulation Up (Reg-Up), Regulation Down (Reg-Down), Responsive Reserve (RRS), Non-Spinning Responsive Reserve (Non-Spin), and ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service (ECRS). The values represent the MCPC generated following each SCED execution over the past 24 hours.\n\n## Day-Ahead Market Prices\n\nDAM Clearing Prices for Capacity\n\nView the Market Clearing Prices for Capacity for all Ancillary Services from the Day-Ahead Market for the last thirty days on a daily basis.\n\nView the Hourly Locational Marginal Prices per electrical bus from the Day-Ahead Market for the last thirty days on a daily basis.\n\nDAM PTP Obligation Results by Settlement Point\n\nView the total amount of PTP Obligation Bids awarded and CRR Offers not awarded in the Day-Ahead Market per Settlement Point where the Settlement Point of the bid or offer is either the Source or the Sink for the last thirty days on a daily basis.\n\nDAM Settlement Point Prices\n\nView the Settlement Point Prices for all Resource Nodes, Load Zones, and Trading Hubs from the Day-Ahead Market for the last thirty days on a daily basis.\n\nView active and binding constraints as well as the associated shadow prices from the Day-Ahead Market for the last thirty days on a daily basis.\n\n## Historical Prices\n\nHistorical DAM Clearing Prices for Capacity\n\nHistorical (by year) of DAM Clearing Prices for Capacity.\n\nHistorical DAM Load Zone and Hub Prices\n\nView DAM Settlement Point Prices (SPPs) for each of the Hubs and Load Zones.\n\nHistorical RTM Clearing Prices for Capacity by 15-Minute Settlement Interval\n\nThis report updates every week for the previous week and shows the 15-minute Real-Time Market Clearing Price for Capacity for each Ancillary Service for each 15-minute Settlement Interval of the previous week.\n\nHistorical RTM Clearing Prices for Capacity by SCED Interval\n\nThis report updates every week for the previous week and shows the Real-Time Market Clearing Prices for Capacity for each Ancillary Service produced by each SCED interval of the previous week.\n\nHistorical RTM Load Zone and Hub Prices\n\nHistorical RTM Settlement Point Prices (SPPs) for each of the Hubs and Load Zones.\n\nHistorical Real-Time Price Adders by SCED Interval\n\nThis report updates every week for the previous week and shows the Real-Time On-Line Reliability Deployment Price Adders for energy and each ancillary service, the total RUC/RMR LDL relaxed, total Load Resource MW deployed that is added to the Demand, total ERS MW deployed that is added to the Demand, total LSL, and total HSL for each SCED interval in the previous week. Previously named: Historical Real Time ORDC and Reliability Deployment Price Adders and Reserves.\n\nHistorical Real-Time Price Adders for 15-Minute Settlement Interval\n\nThis report updates every week for the previous week and shows historical Real-Time On-Line Reliability Deployment Price Adders for energy and each ancillary service type for each 15-minute Settlement Interval of the previous week. Previously named: Historical Real-Time ORDC and Reliability Deployment Prices for 15-minute Settlement Interval.\n\nHistorical Total Capability of Resources Available to Provide Ancillary Services by SCED Interval\n\nThis report updates every week for the previous week and shows the total capability of Resources available to provide the following Ancillary Service combinations, based on the Resource telemetry from the QSE and capped by the limits of the Resource and, for ESRs, further capped by Ancillary Service SCED duration requirements and current available State of Charge (SOC), for all SCED intervals of the previous week.\n\n## Price Corrections\n\nThe Public Notices page displays public notices for Price Corrections for the previous 6 months. Filter Public Notices by Price Corrections Messages to view notices pertaining to:\n\nMarket Price Corrections for the following Markets:\n\n- Day-Ahead\n- Real-Time\n- Supplemental Ancillary Services\n\nFollowing are the Market specific Price Corrections:\n\nDay-Ahead Market price corrections.\n\nReal-Time Market price corrections\n\nSupplemental Ancillary Services Market (SASM) price corrections. Report removed with PR447-03 RTC. Link to remain available until postings have expired.\n\n## Real-Time Prices Reports\n\nLMPs by Electrical Bus\n\nView the Locational Marginal Price for each Electrical Bus, normally produced by SCED every five minutes.\n\nLMPs by Resource Nodes, Load Zones and Trading Hubs\n\nView the Locational Marginal Price for each Settlement Point, normally produced by SCED every five minutes.\n\nRTD Indicative LMPs by Resource Nodes, Load Zones and Hubs\n\nThis report is posted after every Look Ahead RTD run and includes indicative LMPs at Resource Nodes, Hub LMPs and Load Zone for each interval in the Look Ahead SCED-RTD Study Period.\n\nSettlement Point Prices at Resource Nodes, Hubs and Load Zones\n\nView the Settlement Point Price for each Settlement Point, produced from SCED LMPs every 15 minutes.\n\n##### Related Content\n\n###### On this site\n\n- Day-Ahead Market\n- Real-Time Market\n- Business Practice Manual",
